The paper deals with content delivery in a network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of caches and exploiting correlations among contents suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the proposed scheme involves joint cache and channel coding, which may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
